title: Class C track: Maranacook girls, Caribou boys prevail
content: WATERBORO — The Maranacook girls and Caribou boys both withstood strong challenges to win Saturday’s Class C track and field team championships, contested at Massabesic High.    Caribou secured its title by finishing third in the final event of the day, the boys 1,600 relay. Wells won the race and finished second in the team standings, 57-54. Traip was third with 50 points.    Maranacook used a 1-2 finish in the pole vault from Nicole D’Angelo and Janika Pakulski to pull away from a meet-long challenge by Orono. Maranacook scored 103 points. Orono had 92.5. Monmouth was third with 64.    Cayden Spencer-Thompson of Mattanawcook Academy set a meet record in the boys’ long jump with a leap of 23 feet, 1.75 inches.    This story will be updated
